<p>The builtin command for properly indenting the code has already been mentioned (<code>gg=G</code>). If you want to <em>beautify</em> the code, you'll need to use an external application like <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indent_%28Unix%29" rel="noreferrer">indent</a>. Since <code>%</code> denotes the current file in ex mode, you can use it like this:</p>

<pre><code>:!indent %
</code></pre>
